  "prompt": "Can someone get pregnant 10 days after their period?",
  "response": "Yes, it is possible to get pregnant 10 days after the start of your period, depending on the length and regularity of your menstrual cycle. Ovulation typically occurs about 14 days before the start of your next period, which would be around the middle of a typical 28-day cycle. If your cycles are shorter, ovulation could happen earlier. Sperm can live inside the female reproductive system for up to 5 days, so if you have unprotected sex, fertilization can occur if sperm are present when an egg is released. Tracking ovulation through methods such as basal body temperature, ovulation predictor kits, or monitoring cervical mucus can help in understanding your fertile window more precisely. If pregnancy avoidance or achievement is your goal, consider discussing your menstrual cycle and contraceptive options or fertility planning with a healthcare professional.",
